<section id="methods">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="kicker">Method &amp; Robustness</div>
      <h2>The analytic pipeline, step by step.</h2>
      <p class="subtitle">A transparent five-step flow from raw data to validated findings, with explicit robustness evidence.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="method-layout">
      <div class="method-pipeline">
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <div class="step-marker"><span>1</span></div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h4>Phase-stratified repeated cross-sections</h4>
            <p>Data organized into five pandemic phases, enabling structured comparison across changing macro conditions while avoiding false longitudinal claims.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <div class="step-marker"><span>2</span></div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h4>Graphical model estimation</h4>
            <p>Per-phase symptom network estimated via Gaussian graphical model (graphical LASSO), representing conditional dependence among 47 MHQ symptoms.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <div class="step-marker"><span>3</span></div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h4>Community detection &amp; domain alignment</h4>
            <p>Weighted Louvain identifies communities, aligned to a fixed a priori four-domain mapping for comparable, non-circular cross-phase interpretation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <div class="step-marker"><span>4</span></div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h4>Exact minimum dominating sets &amp; control metrics</h4>
            <p>All minimum-cardinality dominating sets enumerated exactly, yielding node-level control frequency and module-level ACF and AMCS measures.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <div class="step-marker"><span>5</span></div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h4>Resampling, case-dropping &amp; replication</h4>
            <p>Bootstrap variation, case-loss stability, and India cohort replication with phase-wise downsampling to separate robust signals from noise.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="method-right">
        <div class="panel robustness-panel">
          <h3>Metric stability at 60% case retention</h3>
          <p class="rob-subtitle">Mean replicate-to-baseline correlation across all phases</p>
          <div class="rob-bars">
            <div class="rob-row">
              <span class="rob-label">Strength</span>
              <div class="rob-track"><div class="rob-fill" style="width: 83.8%; background: var(--spf);"></div></div>
              <span class="rob-val good">0.838</span>
            </div>
            <div class="rob-row">
              <span class="rob-label">AMCS</span>
              <div class="rob-track"><div class="rob-fill" style="width: 73.7%; background: var(--emo);"></div></div>
              <span class="rob-val moderate">0.737</span>
            </div>
            <div class="rob-row">
              <span class="rob-label">ACF</span>
              <div class="rob-track"><div class="rob-fill" style="width: 33.9%; background: var(--str);"></div></div>
              <span class="rob-val weak">0.339</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="rob-note">This hierarchy explains why the manuscript emphasizes AMCS over ACF for cross-phase comparison.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="evidence-grid">
          <div class="panel evidence-item">
            <h4>Replication</h4>
            <p>India cohort and phase-wise downsampling show patterns aren't an artifact of one country or sample size.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="panel evidence-item">
            <h4>Metric discipline</h4>
            <p>Node strength and AMCS are stable; ACF is explicitly flagged as more sensitive to case loss.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="panel evidence-item">
            <h4>Bounded inference</h4>
            <p>Cross-sectional design, conditional dependencies (not causal), and exploratory macro links.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="method-figure figure-block">
          <img src="/covid-mcn-site/figs/fig6.png" alt="Fig. 6 — Robustness analysis" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="figure-caption">Fig. 6 — Bootstrap stability and case-dropping robustness</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

